data.title: Queensland place names search
meta_keywords: place names; search map for place names; Queensland place names search; queensland place names database; QPN; addresses; place names databases
data.meta_description: Search the database and find details of all official and some unofficial place names in Queensland.
data.text:
Search tips

Search

Enter search term and select Search button, you will then be able to filter your results by place type.

A search for 'Clare' will include results for 'Clare', and 'Claremont Rock', and 'Lake Clarendon'.

A search for 'Moon' will include results for 'Moons Hill', 'Moonjaree', 'Goongoomoonee' and 'Killymoon'.

Enter 'mt' as 'mount' (e.g. 'Mount Barney').

Enter 'pt' as 'point' (e.g. 'Point Lookout').

Enter 'saint' as 'st' (e.g. 'St George') or as 'saint' (e.g. 'Saint Smith Range').

1000 results is the maximum search result. Please consider revising or filtering your search if 1000 results are returned.

Filters

"Select place type" in the filter box and select Update button. Select another place type from the filter box to add additional place types. Select Update button to add the type to your search results.

To see all place types enter * in the "Enter search term" box and select Search. Filters may then be used to see all names of the selected place type(s).

Map

When there are multiple instances of a place in a small area this icon will appear. Zooming in will reveal these clustered results. Clicking on the icon will zoom in to that area.
